  "prompt": "How do I capture raw images from an Android camera?",
  "response": "Capturing raw images on Android involves using the `Camera2` API. Here's a breakdown of the process, along with code examples and important considerations:\n\n**1. Project Setup and Permissions:**\n\n*   **Permissions:**  You'll need to request the following permissions in your `AndroidManifest.xml`:\n\n    ```xml\n    <uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.CAMERA\" />\n    <uses-feature android:name=\"android.hardware.camera\" android:required=\"true\" />\n    <uses-feature android:name=\"android.hardware.camera.raw\" android:required=\"true\" />\n    <uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE\" /> <!-- For saving the DNG file -->\n    ```\n\n    *   `android.permission.CAMERA`:  Essential for accessing the camera.\n    *   `android.hardware.camera`: Indicates that the app uses a camera.\n    *   `android.hardware.camera.raw`: Important! This specifies that you require the ability to capture RAW (DNG) images. The app won't be installable on devices that don't support RAW capture.\n    *   `android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE`:  Required if you intend to save the DNG files to external storage.  Remember to request runtime permissions for this on Android 6.0 (Marshmallow) and later.\n\n*   **Runtime Permissions:**  On Android 6.0 and above, you must request the `CAMERA` and `WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE` permissions at runtime.  Use `ActivityCompat.requestPermissions` to prompt the user.\n\n    ```kotlin\n    private val CAMERA_PERMISSION_REQUEST_CODE = 100\n    private val STORAGE_PERMISSION_REQUEST_CODE = 101\n    private fun checkAndRequestPermissions() {\n        val cameraPermission = ContextCompat.checkSelfPermission(this, Manifest.permission.CAMERA)\n        val storagePermission = ContextCompat.checkSelfPermission(this, Manifest.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE)\n\n        val permissionsToRequest = mutableListOf<String>()\n\n        if (cameraPermission != PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED) {\n            permissionsToRequest.add(Manifest.permission.CAMERA)\n        }\n\n        if (storagePermission != PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED) {\n            permissionsToRequest.add(Manifest.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE)\n        }\n\n        if (permissionsToRequest.isNotEmpty()) {\n            ActivityCompat.requestPermissions(this, permissionsToRequest.toTypedArray(), CAMERA_PERMISSION_REQUEST_CODE)\n        } else {\n            // Permissions already granted, proceed\n            openCamera()\n        }\n    }\n\n\n    override fun onRequestPermissionsResult(\n        requestCode: Int,\n        permissions: Array<String>,\n        grantResults: IntArray\n    ) {\n        super.onRequestPermissionsResult(requestCode, permissions, grantResults)\n        when (requestCode) {\n            CAMERA_PERMISSION_REQUEST_CODE -> {\n                if ((grantResults.isNotEmpty() && grantResults[0] == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED)) {\n                    // Camera permission granted.  Now check for storage.\n                    if (ContextCompat.checkSelfPermission(this, Manifest.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE) != PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED) {\n                        ActivityCompat.requestPermissions(this, arrayOf(Manifest.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE), STORAGE_PERMISSION_REQUEST_CODE)\n                    } else {\n                        //Both Camera and Storage Permission granted\n                         openCamera()\n                    }\n\n                } else {\n                    // Camera permission denied.  Inform the user.\n                    Toast.makeText(this, \"Camera permission is required.\", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()\n                }\n            }\n            STORAGE_PERMISSION_REQUEST_CODE -> {\n                if ((grantResults.isNotEmpty() && grantResults[0] == PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED)) {\n                    // Storage permission granted\n                     openCamera()\n\n                } else {\n                    // Storage permission denied.  Inform the user.\n                    Toast.makeText(this, \"Storage permission is required.\", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    ```\n\n**2. Camera2 API Setup:**\n\n*   **`CameraManager`:**  Use `getSystemService(Context.CAMERA_SERVICE) as CameraManager` to get an instance of the `CameraManager`.\n\n*   **`CameraCharacteristics`:**  Get the `CameraCharacteristics` for the camera you want to use using `cameraManager.getCameraCharacteristics(cameraId)`. This allows you to query the camera's capabilities, including RAW support, available resolutions, and more.\n\n*   **Check for RAW Support:**  Crucially, check if the camera supports RAW capture using `characteristics.get(CameraCharacteristics.REQUEST_AVAILABLE_CAPABILITIES)`.  Verify that `CameraCharacteristics.REQUEST_AVAILABLE_CAPABILITIES_RAW` is included in the returned array.\n\n*   **Select Camera ID:** Choose which camera to use (front or back).  Iterate through `cameraManager.cameraIdList` and inspect the `CameraCharacteristics` of each camera to find a suitable one.\n\n    ```kotlin\n    private var cameraId: String? = null\n    private var cameraDevice: CameraDevice? = null\n    private lateinit var cameraManager: CameraManager\n    private var imageReader: ImageReader? = null\n    private var captureSession: CameraCaptureSession? = null\n    private var backgroundThread: HandlerThread? = null\n    private var backgroundHandler: Handler? = null\n\n    private fun selectCamera(): Boolean {\n        cameraManager = getSystemService(Context.CAMERA_SERVICE) as CameraManager\n\n        try {\n            for (id in cameraManager.cameraIdList) {\n                val characteristics = cameraManager.getCameraCharacteristics(id)\n                val facing = characteristics.get(CameraCharacteristics.LENS_FACING)\n\n                // Choose the back-facing camera (you can modify this)\n                if (facing == CameraCharacteristics.LENS_FACING_BACK) {\n                    //Check if the camera supports RAW\n                     val capabilities = characteristics.get(CameraCharacteristics.REQUEST_AVAILABLE_CAPABILITIES)\n                        if (capabilities != null && capabilities.contains(CameraCharacteristics.REQUEST_AVAILABLE_CAPABILITIES_RAW)) {\n                            cameraId = id\n                            return true\n                        } else {\n                            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Camera $id does not support RAW capture\")\n                        }\n                }\n            }\n        } catch (e: CameraAccessException) {\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Error accessing camera: ${e.message}\")\n        }\n        return false // No suitable camera found.\n    }\n    ```\n\n*   **Choose a DNG Resolution:**  Use `characteristics.get(CameraCharacteristics.SCALER_STREAM_CONFIGURATION_MAP)` to get the available stream configurations and choose a suitable resolution for DNG capture.  Pick a resolution that's supported for `ImageFormat.RAW_SENSOR`.\n\n    ```kotlin\n    private fun chooseRawResolution(characteristics: CameraCharacteristics): Size? {\n        val map = characteristics.get(CameraCharacteristics.SCALER_STREAM_CONFIGURATION_MAP) ?: return null\n        val rawSizes = map.getOutputSizes(ImageFormat.RAW_SENSOR)\n        return rawSizes.maxByOrNull { it.width * it.height } // Choose the largest resolution\n    }\n    ```\n\n*   **`ImageReader`:** Create an `ImageReader` to receive the RAW (DNG) image data.  Specify `ImageFormat.RAW_SENSOR` as the format and the chosen resolution.\n\n    ```kotlin\n     private fun setupImageReader(width: Int, height: Int) {\n        imageReader = ImageReader.newInstance(width, height, ImageFormat.RAW_SENSOR, 1) // Only need 1 image at a time\n        imageReader?.setOnImageAvailableListener({ reader ->\n            val image = reader.acquireNextImage()\n            image?.let {\n                saveRawImage(it)\n                it.close()\n            }\n        }, backgroundHandler)\n    }\n\n    ```\n\n*   **`CameraDevice.StateCallback`:**  Implement a `CameraDevice.StateCallback` to handle camera opening and closing.\n\n    ```kotlin\n    private val stateCallback = object : CameraDevice.StateCallback() {\n        override fun onOpened(camera: CameraDevice) {\n            cameraDevice = camera\n            createCaptureSession()\n        }\n\n        override fun onDisconnected(camera: CameraDevice) {\n            cameraDevice?.close()\n            cameraDevice = null\n        }\n\n        override fun onError(camera: CameraDevice, error: Int) {\n            cameraDevice?.close()\n            cameraDevice = null\n            // Handle camera errors appropriately.\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Camera error: $error\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    private fun openCamera() {\n\n        if (!selectCamera()) {\n            Toast.makeText(this, \"No suitable camera found.\", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()\n            return\n        }\n\n         // Start background thread\n        backgroundThread = HandlerThread(\"CameraBackground\")\n        backgroundThread?.start()\n        backgroundHandler = Handler(backgroundThread?.looper)\n\n        try {\n            cameraManager.openCamera(cameraId!!, stateCallback, backgroundHandler)\n        } catch (e: CameraAccessException) {\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Error opening camera: ${e.message}\")\n        } catch (e: SecurityException) {\n             Toast.makeText(this, \"Camera permission not granted!\", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()\n             Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Camera permission not granted: ${e.message}\")\n        }\n    }\n    ```\n\n**3. Create a Capture Session:**\n\n*   **`CameraCaptureSession.StateCallback`:** Implement a `CameraCaptureSession.StateCallback` to handle session creation and configuration.\n\n*   **`CaptureRequest.Builder`:**  Create a `CaptureRequest.Builder` using `cameraDevice.createCaptureRequest(CameraDevice.TEMPLATE_STILL_CAPTURE)`.  This configures the camera for a single still capture.\n\n*   **`addTarget()`:**  Add the `ImageReader`'s surface as a target for the capture request using `captureRequestBuilder.addTarget(imageReader.surface)`.\n\n*   **`set()`:**  Set the necessary capture settings.  Crucially, set `CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE` to `CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE_ON` for correct DNG processing (if supported by the device).  Also, set `CaptureRequest.NOISE_REDUCTION_MODE` to `CaptureRequest.NOISE_REDUCTION_MODE_OFF` to avoid post-processing of the RAW image. Adjust other settings like white balance and exposure as needed.\n\n    ```kotlin\n    private fun createCaptureSession() {\n        val size = chooseRawResolution(cameraManager.getCameraCharacteristics(cameraId!!))\n        if (size == null) {\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Could not determine raw resolution\")\n            return\n        }\n        setupImageReader(size.width, size.height)\n\n        try {\n            val targets = listOf(imageReader?.surface)\n\n            cameraDevice?.createCaptureSession(targets, object : CameraCaptureSession.StateCallback() {\n                override fun onConfigured(session: CameraCaptureSession) {\n                    captureSession = session\n                    captureStillImage()\n                }\n\n                override fun onConfigureFailed(session: CameraCaptureSession) {\n                    Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Capture session configuration failed\")\n                }\n            }, backgroundHandler)\n\n        } catch (e: CameraAccessException) {\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Error creating capture session: ${e.message}\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    ```\n\n**4. Capture the Image:**\n\n*   **`capture()` or `captureBurst()`:**  Call `captureSession.capture(captureRequest, captureCallback, backgroundHandler)` to capture a single image. Use `captureBurst()` for a sequence of captures.\n\n*   **`CaptureCallback`:**  Implement a `CaptureCallback` to handle the capture result.  This is where you can check for errors and get information about the capture.\n\n    ```kotlin\n    private fun captureStillImage() {\n        try {\n            val captureRequestBuilder = cameraDevice?.createCaptureRequest(CameraDevice.TEMPLATE_STILL_CAPTURE)\n            captureRequestBuilder?.addTarget(imageReader!!.surface)\n\n            // RAW Specific Settings\n            captureRequestBuilder?.set(CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE, CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE_ON) // Important for DNG\n            captureRequestBuilder?.set(CaptureRequest.NOISE_REDUCTION_MODE, CaptureRequest.NOISE_REDUCTION_MODE_OFF) // to keep it raw\n\n            // Auto focus should be done before capture still image.\n            captureRequestBuilder?.set(CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AF_MODE,CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AF_MODE_CONTINUOUS_PICTURE )\n\n\n            captureSession?.capture(captureRequestBuilder?.build()!!, object : CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback() {\n                override fun onCaptureCompleted(session: CameraCaptureSession, request: CaptureRequest, result: TotalCaptureResult) {\n                    super.onCaptureCompleted(session, request, result)\n                    Log.d(\"Camera\", \"Capture completed\")\n                }\n            }, backgroundHandler)\n\n        } catch (e: CameraAccessException) {\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Error capturing still image: ${e.message}\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    ```\n\n**5. Saving the DNG:**\n\n*   **`Image.getPlanes()` and `ByteBuffer`:**  In the `OnImageAvailableListener` of the `ImageReader`, get the RAW image data from the `Image` object.  The RAW image data is typically in the `Image.Plane` array.\n\n*   **`DngCreator`:**  Use the `android.hardware.camera2.DngCreator` class to create a DNG (Digital Negative) file from the RAW data. This class takes the `CameraCharacteristics` and the `Image` as input.\n\n*   **Write to File:**  Write the DNG data to a file.\n\n    ```kotlin\n     private fun saveRawImage(image: Image) {\n        val file = File(Environment.getExternalStoragePublicDirectory(Environment.DIRECTORY_DCIM), \"raw_image_${System.currentTimeMillis()}.dng\")\n\n        try {\n            val outputStream = FileOutputStream(file)\n            val dngCreator = DngCreator(cameraManager.getCameraCharacteristics(cameraId!!), image)\n            dngCreator.writeImage(outputStream)\n            outputStream.close()\n            Log.d(\"Camera\", \"DNG saved to ${file.absolutePath}\")\n\n        } catch (e: IOException) {\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Error saving DNG: ${e.message}\")\n        }\n    }\n\n    ```\n\n**6. Clean Up:**\n\n*   **Close Resources:**  In your `onPause()` or `onDestroy()` methods, close the `CameraDevice`, `ImageReader`, and `CameraCaptureSession` to release resources. Stop the background thread.\n\n    ```kotlin\n    override fun onPause() {\n        super.onPause()\n        closeCamera()\n        stopBackgroundThread()\n    }\n\n    private fun closeCamera() {\n        captureSession?.close()\n        captureSession = null\n        cameraDevice?.close()\n        cameraDevice = null\n        imageReader?.close()\n        imageReader = null\n    }\n\n    private fun stopBackgroundThread() {\n        backgroundThread?.quitSafely()\n        try {\n            backgroundThread?.join()\n            backgroundThread = null\n            backgroundHandler = null\n        } catch (e: InterruptedException) {\n            Log.e(\"Camera\", \"Error stopping background thread: ${e.message}\")\n        }\n    }\n    ```\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Device Support:** Not all Android devices support RAW capture.  The `android.hardware.camera.raw` feature in the manifest ensures your app only runs on devices that support it. Check for `CameraCharacteristics.REQUEST_AVAILABLE_CAPABILITIES_RAW` at runtime for extra safety.\n*   **Permissions:** Properly handle runtime permissions for the camera and storage.\n*   **Error Handling:**  Thoroughly handle exceptions that can occur during camera operations (e.g., `CameraAccessException`).\n*   **Background Thread:**  Perform camera operations on a background thread to avoid blocking the UI thread.\n*   **Resolution:** The RAW resolution may be different from the JPEG resolution.  Choose a suitable resolution that's supported for `ImageFormat.RAW_SENSOR`.\n*   **DNG Metadata:** The `DngCreator` automatically populates the DNG file with metadata from the `CameraCharacteristics`.\n*   **Lens Shading Map:**  Setting `CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE` to `CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_LENS_SHADING_MAP_MODE_ON` is crucial for correct color and shading in the DNG, as it provides the lens shading correction data.  If the device doesn't support it, you'll need to handle lens shading correction yourself, which is complex.\n*   **Memory:**  RAW images are large.  Make sure you have enough memory to handle them, and consider writing them to external storage directly.\n*   **Post-Processing:** RAW images require post-processing to become viewable. You'll need to use photo editing software (e.g., Adobe Lightroom, RawTherapee, Darktable) or a custom processing pipeline to develop them.\n\nThis comprehensive guide will help you capture RAW images on Android.  Remember to adapt the code snippets to your specific application needs and thoroughly test your implementation.  Good luck!\n",
